1. Agile Methodology

Agile Methodology is a software development approach that focuses on delivering software in small, incremental releases while continuously incorporating customer feedback. It emphasizes collaboration, flexibility, and rapid delivery of working software.

Key Principles of Agile

1. Customer satisfaction through continuous delivery of valuable software.


2. Welcome changing requirements, even late in development.


3. Deliver working software frequently.


4. Business stakeholders and developers work together regularly.


5. Build projects around motivated individuals.


6. Working software is the primary measure of progress.


7. Maintain a sustainable development pace.


8. Continuous attention to technical excellence and good design.



Agile Lifecycle

1. Requirement Gathering

Collect and prioritize requirements from stakeholders.



2. Sprint Planning

Divide work into small iterations called sprints (usually 1–4 weeks).



3. Development

Developers build the features planned for the sprint.



4. Testing

QA team tests the developed features to identify defects.



5. Review/Demo

Completed work is demonstrated to stakeholders for feedback.



6. Retrospective

Team discusses what went well and what can be improved.



7. Release

The tested software is released to users.




Agile Artifacts

Product Backlog

Sprint Backlog

User Stories

Burndown Chart

Increment


Agile Roles

Product Owner – Manages requirements and priorities.

Scrum Master – Facilitates Agile processes and removes blockers.

Development Team – Develops and tests the software.


Advantages of Agile

Faster delivery of software.

Better customer satisfaction.

Flexibility to handle changing requirements.

Improved product quality.

Early detection of issues.


Example

Suppose a company wants to develop an online shopping application. Instead of building the entire application at once, Agile delivers features in phases:

Sprint 1: User Registration & Login

Sprint 2: Product Catalog

Sprint 3: Shopping Cart

Sprint 4: Payment Gateway


This allows customers to review and provide feedback after each sprint.


