2. Monitoring Activity

Monitoring Activity is the process of continuously tracking and reviewing project progress, application performance, testing activities, or system operations to ensure everything is functioning as expected and project goals are being achieved.

Purpose of Monitoring

Track project progress.

Identify issues and risks early.

Ensure tasks are completed on time.

Maintain software quality.

Improve team productivity.


Monitoring Activities in Software Testing

1. Test Progress Monitoring

Track executed, passed, failed, and blocked test cases.



2. Defect Monitoring

Monitor defect status such as Open, Assigned, Fixed, Retest, Closed, and Reopened.



3. Schedule Monitoring

Compare actual progress against planned timelines.



4. Resource Monitoring

Ensure team members are effectively utilized.



5. Risk Monitoring

Identify potential risks and take preventive actions.




Monitoring Metrics

Number of Test Cases Executed

Test Pass Percentage

Defect Density

Defect Leakage

Test Coverage

Sprint Velocity


Example

A QA team has 100 test cases:

Executed: 80

Passed: 70

Failed: 10

Pending: 20


By monitoring these metrics daily, the team can determine whether testing is on track and identify areas needing attention.

Benefits of Monitoring

Early identification of issues.

Better project control.

Improved decision-making.

Increased software quality.

Timely delivery of projects.


